# Sentinel — Comprehensive Codebase Review

## 1. Project Overview

Sentinel is an AI-powered observability platform with a **prompt firewall** for sanitizing sensitive log data before sending it to LLMs. The architecture follows a microservices pattern using TypeScript, Kafka, Knex (PostgreSQL), Redis, and an API Gateway.

### Services
| Service | Port | Role |
|---|---|---|
| API Gateway | 3000 | Proxy, auth, rate-limiting, caching |
| User Service | 4000 | User CRUD, register/login with JWT |
| Incident Service | 4001 | Incident CRUD + Kafka consumers |
| Firewall Service | 4002 | Log ingestion, sanitization, AI analysis |
| Audit Service | 4003 | Kafka consumer for audit logs + alerts |
| Notification Service | 4004 | Kafka consumer → Slack + Email |

### Infrastructure
- **Kafka** (with Zookeeper) for event-driven communication
- **Redis** for caching and rate limiting
- **PostgreSQL** (shared DB via `@shared/utils`)
- **Docker Compose** for orchestration

