## 3. Event Flow Diagram (Your Intended Architecture)

```mermaid
sequenceDiagram
    participant C as Client
    participant FW as Firewall Service
    participant K as Kafka
    participant IS as Incident Service
    participant AI as AI Worker (in FW)
    participant AS as Audit Service
    participant NS as Notification Service

    C->>FW: POST /api/ingest (raw logs)
    FW->>FW: sanitizeLogs() + policy check
    FW->>K: produce "incident.created"

    K->>IS: consume "incident.created"
    IS->>IS: Store in DB (uuid incident_id)
    IS->>K: produce "incident.stored"
    IS->>K: produce "alert.created"

    K->>AI: consume "incident.stored"
    AI->>FW: POST /api/analyze (internal HTTP)
    FW->>FW: Gemini AI analysis
    AI->>K: produce "incident.analyzed"

    K->>IS: consume "incident.analyzed"
    IS->>IS: Update ai_summary in DB
    IS->>K: produce "audit.event"
    IS->>K: produce "alert.created"

    K->>AS: consume "audit.event"
    AS->>AS: Store audit_logs in DB

    K->>AS: consume "alert.created"
    AS->>AS: Store alert in DB

    K->>NS: consume "alert.created"
    NS->>NS: Send Slack + Email
    NS->>NS: Store system_event in DB
```

